HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 115
BY REPRESENTATIVES KNOX, WILFORD CARTER, AND MILLER
A RESOLUTION
To designate Wednesday, April 8, 2026, as Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Incorporated, Day
at the state capitol.
WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Incorporated, is celebrating one hundred
fifteen years of achievement; the great state of Louisiana has fashioned two grand
polemarchs: Richard B. Millspaugh, the seventeenth Grand Polemarch, and Dwayne M.
Murray, Esq., the thirty-first Grand Polemarch; and
WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Incorporated, is comprised of undergraduate
and alumni chapters on major college campuses and in cities throughout the country; the
fraternity was established on January 5, 1911, on the campus of Indiana University at
Bloomington, Indiana, and its establishment effectively planted the seed of a fraternal tree
whose fruit is now available to college men everywhere, regardless of color, religion, or
national origin; and
WHEREAS, the constitution of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Incorporated, is dedicated
to the principles of achievement and service; from its inception, every endeavor of the
fraternity was directed towards establishing a strong foundation before embarking on plans
of expansion; and
WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity was originally chartered and incorporated
as Kappa Alpha Nu on May 15, 1911, and the name was changed to Kappa Alpha Psi by a
resolution offered and adopted at the Grand Chapter meeting in December 1914, which
became effective April 15, 1915; and
