WHEREAS, except for the years of World War I and World War II, during which
time several Grand Chapter meetings were suspended, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity embarked
upon an era of expansion and growth; and
WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Incorporated, is now organizationally and
administratively mature, and the fraternity steadily moves toward a tomorrow of promise,
productivity, and influence.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Wednesday, April 8, 2026, as Kappa Alpha
Psi Fraternity, Incorporated, Day at the state capitol and does hereby extend sincerest wishes
that the organization continue to prosper in all of its endeavors for many years to come.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
